Global Medical Non-Woven Fabric Folding Machine Market Insights
Medical Non-Woven Fabric Folding Machine Market size was valued at USD 0.85 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 1.50 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Medical Non-Woven Fabric Folding Machine Market Overview
The global medical non-woven fabric folding machine market has witnessed substantial growth due to the increasing demand for non-woven fabrics in medical and hygiene applications. The market size was valued at USD 1.45 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.5% from 2025 to 2032. Non-woven fabrics are widely used in surgical gowns, face masks, wipes, and other medical products, driving the demand for folding machines that provide efficient, high-speed, and consistent folding solutions. Technological advancements, including automation and energy-efficient systems, are expected to further support market growth.

